<body><p>GE.12-13566 
</p>
<p><b>Human Rights Council 
Twentieth session 
</b></p>
<p>Agenda item 7 
</p>
<p><b>Human rights situation in Palestine and other  
</b></p>
<p><b>occupied Arab territories 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Progress report of the United Nations High Commissioner 
for Human Rights on the implementation of Human Rights 
Council resolution 19/18 
</b></p>
<p>1. The present report is submitted in accordance with paragraph 6 of Human Rights 
</p>
<p>Council resolution 19/18, in which the Council requested the United Nations High 
</p>
<p>Commissioner for Human Rights to submit to the Council, at its twentieth session, a 
</p>
<p>progress report on the implementation of that resolution. The reporting period was from the 
</p>
<p>date of adoption of resolution 19/18, 22 March 2012, to 7 May 2012.   
</p>
<p>2. In order to follow up on the implementation of resolution 19/18 within the reporting 
</p>
<p>period, the Office of the High Commissioner (OHCHR) sent notes verbales and other 
</p>
<p>communications to key interlocutors to which the United Nations independent international 
</p>
<p>fact-finding mission on the Gaza conflict addressed recommendations in its report 
</p>
<p>(A/HRC/12/48).  In the light of paragraph 2 of resolution 19/18, OHCHR also sent a note 
</p>
<p>verbale to the Permanent Mission of Switzerland to the United Nations Office and other 
</p>
<p>international organizations in Geneva.   
</p>
<p>3. The purpose of the above-mentioned notes verbales and other communications was 
</p>
<p>to request information regarding measures taken or envisaged to be taken in order to 
</p>
<p>implement the recommendations made by the fact-finding mission, as well as detailed 
</p>
<p>information on non-implementation and on other measures required to ensure the most 
</p>
<p>adequate and effective implementation of the said recommendations. The information 
</p>
<p>received in response, as well as information gathered from publicly available sources, will 
</p>
<p>form the basis of the report of the Secretary-General, which will be submitted to the 
</p>
<p>Council at its twenty-first session, pursuant to paragraph 5 of resolution 19/18. 
</p>
<p>    
</p>
<p> 
United Nations A/HRC/20/36 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p><b>General Assembly 
</b></p>
